    "en": {
      "title": "Big news from the European Union",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The EU has condemned the use of unnecessary force on peaceful protesters and stressed the importance of the right to peaceful assembly.",
        "In the report published by the European Union, some other issues including this issue have been mentioned.",
        "The European Union has noted that the protection of human rights and the rule of law through reconciliation and good governance is essential.",
        "As the Parliament of Sri Lanka took urgent steps to appoint Ranil Wickremesinghe as the new President, the Union emphasized the need to establish the freedom of expression and individual rights of the people of Sri Lanka in a democratic and peaceful manner.",
        "Furthermore, Sri Lanka's new government has signaled strongly that it expects full compliance with its GSP Plus commitments.",
        "The GSP Plus offer, reintroduced in 2017, is essential for Sri Lanka's economic growth and \u20ac70 million worth of cooperation projects are being streamlined.",
        "The statement also stated that the European Union will continue to support all efforts in favor of the people of Sri Lanka."
      ],
